<p>A crime has been committed, and it is known that the criminal is part is part of a population of 6 million. Through research, the police know that only one person in a million has DNA that matches the DNA of the perpetrator. A suspect is found. Define the events<br />
* <em>A</em> = the person’s DNA matches the offender’s DNA.
* <em>B</em> = the person found is innocent.  Then what is the probability that the person found is innocent and his DNA matches that of the perpetrator?</p>
</p>]]></text>
